OASISFormat: 0.4
AlphaFeatures: ocamlbuild_more_args, disable_oasis_section
OCamlVersion: >= 3.12.0
Name: bitmasks
Version: 1.0.0
License: BSD-3-clause with OCaml linking exception
Synopsis: BitMasks over int and int64 exposed as sets
Description:
  Library for exposing bitmasks (typically as int or int64) in an implementation compatible with
  OCaml's Set. The underlying data representation is unaltered, allowing the value to be manipulated
  either as a bitmask or as a set without conversion.
Authors: David Allsopp
Maintainers: David Allsopp <david.allsopp@metastack.com>
Homepage: http://foo.example.com
Copyrights: (c) 2013-2014 MetaStack Solutions Ltd.
#Categories: 
Plugins: META (0.4), StdFiles (0.4), DevFiles (0.4)
BuildTools: ocamlbuild
# TODO Want to be able to specify a variable for the value of XStdFilesINSTALLFilename rather than INSTALL.txt
DisableOASISSection: INSTALL.txt
XStdFilesAUTHORS: false
XStdFilesREADME: false

Library bitmasks
  Path: .
  Modules: BitMaskSet

